  <preparation>Combine garlic, jalapeno, lime juice, water and salt and blend until well mixed.  Marinate tri-tip overnight before removing to de-chill.


Prepare 500F oven.  Remove roast from marinade and reserve marinade.  Dubiously: oil tri-tip before placing in a roasting pan, fat-side up, and including up to 1/2" of marinade into the roasting pan.  Cook for 20-40 minutes, as necessary.

Sauce: Sautee mushrooms, onion and garlic in olive oil until softened.   Add wine to a volume sufficient to allow mushrooms to absorb most fluid.</preparation>
